about.summary: A programmatic interface to many species occurrence data sources, including Global Biodiversity Information Facility ('GBIF'), 'USGSs' Biodiversity Information Serving Our Nation ('BISON'), 'iNaturalist', Berkeley 'Ecoinformatics' Engine, 'eBird', Integrated Digitized 'Biocollections' ('iDigBio'), 'VertNet', Ocean 'Biogeographic' Information System ('OBIS'), and Atlas of Living Australia ('ALA'). Includes functionality for retrieving species occurrence data, and combining those data.

name: r-spocc
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "1.0.8" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-spocc
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/spocc_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/spocc/spocc_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 59248d7eb692524ef89366c1e63df89332c811adcc391200b9ecf28fba7aa917

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 1
  noarch: generic
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ posix }}zip              # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-crul >=0.3.4
    - r-data.table >=1.9.6
    - r-jsonlite >=1.4
    - r-lubridate >=1.5.0
    - r-rbison >=0.6.0
    - r-rebird >=1.0.0
    - r-rgbif >=1.0.0
    - r-ridigbio >=0.3.5
    - r-rvertnet >=0.7.0
    - r-tibble >=1.2
    - r-whisker >=0.3_2
    - r-wicket >=0.3.0
  run:
    - r-base
    - r-crul >=0.3.4
    - r-data.table >=1.9.6
    - r-jsonlite >=1.4
    - r-lubridate >=1.5.0
    - r-rbison >=0.6.0
    - r-rebird >=1.0.0
    - r-rgbif >=1.0.0
    - r-ridigbio >=0.3.5
    - r-rvertnet >=0.7.0
    - r-tibble >=1.2
    - r-whisker >=0.3_2
    - r-wicket >=0.3.0

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('spocc')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('spocc')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/ropensci/spocc (devel), https://ropensci.github.io/spocc/ (user
    manual)
  license: MIT
  summary: A programmatic interface to many species occurrence data sources, including Global
    Biodiversity Information Facility ('GBIF'), 'USGSs' Biodiversity Information Serving
    Our Nation ('BISON'), 'iNaturalist', Berkeley 'Ecoinformatics' Engine, 'eBird',
    Integrated Digitized 'Biocollections' ('iDigBio'), 'VertNet', Ocean 'Biogeographic'
    Information System ('OBIS'), and Atlas of Living Australia ('ALA'). Includes functionality
    for retrieving species occurrence data, and combining those data.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT'
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
